  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.19.1\n\n### What happened?\n\nI am trying to set mapping values in a contract. When calling `hardhat_setStorageAt`, if the storage slot value begins with `0x0...`, I get the error `InvalidArgumentsError: Errors encountered in param 1: Invalid value \"0x0...\" supplied to : QUANTITY`\r\n\r\nit seems like this stems from the [validateParams](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/core/jsonrpc/types/input/validation.ts#L15) function because the storage slot result returns [result.isLeft()](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/core/jsonrpc/types/input/validation.ts#L61C20-L61C46) but I had trouble diagnosing further from there\r\n\r\nYou can see here that trying to call `hardhat_setStorageAt` with 2 `0x0...` values fails\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/assets/114708157/2bd55767-e509-45de-b7c6-6dcf9b2ec3e9)\r\n\r\nHowever, only having 1 `0x0...` storage slot value causes that call to pass\r\n![image](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/assets/114708157/462e69b6-d282-42ce-b6a9-8bc85bbbfe2a)\r\n\r\nWhen both storage slots are non `0x0...`, both calls pass\r\n![image](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/assets/114708157/f170a11b-17cf-489e-9e80-6ace1dc7c297)\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\ncall `await hre.network.provider.send(\"hardhat_setStorageAt\", [<address>, <0x0... storage slot>, <any non 0 amount>])`\r\n\r\ntip: storage slots for mappings in solidity are dictated with `utils.keccak256(utils.defaultAbiCoder.encode([`<mapping key type>`, `uint256`], [<mapping key>, slotNumber]))`\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
